{"Q0":"Over time I noticed the patterns were ranked, so I gave them names and tried to remember where they were in the ranks. The leopard print was always the preferred one, so it was at the top and the checkered one was all the way at the bottom. If I recall correctly the ranking was Leopard Print, Bloop (The mostly yellow/gold pattern), Green, Swirly (The blue with the yellow loopy pattern), Pink, Cross (Multi-colored with yellow x or cross shape in the middle), and then Checkered. I tried to think of them in a lineup and identify which one was higher up. There were some mistakes due to mistypes or time."}

{"Q0":"I don't think I really had a strategy to learn it. It took me a while to really notice a pattern. Once I did, I tried to remember in a disorganized way, thinking \"okay, Green over Pink, Green over Cross, Pink over Cross, Swirly over Pink\", but I was trying to remember which pattern was preferred in a specific pairing. When I mentally ranked them instead and identified a pattern's placement in the whole lineup rather than how it related only to the other image being shown, it became much easier."}

{"Q0":"I was super confused when I first started choosing images because the right choice seemed arbitrary before I noticed the pattern, but I think that was intentional. If it was, then everything was quite clear."}
